<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
   <title>Reference rendering - no red, bold italic small-caps Ahem</title>
   <link href="https://opera.com" rel="author" title="Opera Software" />
   <style type="text/css">
      #outer {
         position: relative;
      }
      #inner1, #inner2 {
         position: absolute;
         top: 0px;
         left: 0px;
         font-family: "Ahem";
         font-size: 96px;
         font-style: italic;
         font-variant: small-caps;
         font-weight: bold;
      }
      #inner1 {
         color: red;
      }
      #inner2 {
         color: black;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p>Test passes if there is no red visible on the page except for
   antialiasing.</p>
   <div id="outer">
      <div id="inner1">a</div>
      <div id="inner2">b</div>
   </div>


</body></html>